04613nam a22005895i 9780300142488DE-B159720230529094047.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20092009ctu    fo  d z      eng d  a97803001424887 a10.12987/97803001424882doi  a(DE-B1597)485451  a(OCoLC)402597113  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  actucUS-CT 7aLAN0000002bisacsh04a895.1/3522221 aCan Xue, Can, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFive Spice Street /cCan Can Xue. 1aNew Haven, CT : bYale University Press, c[2009] 4c©2009  a1 online resource (320 p.) :b0  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aThe Margellos World Republic of Letters00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tPreliminaries -- t1. Madam X’s Age and Mr. Q’s Looks -- t2. Madam X’s Occupations -- t3. Madam X’s and the Widow’s Differing Opinions about ‘‘Sex’’ -- t4. Mr. Q and His Family -- t5. The Failure of Reeducation -- t6. Madam X Talks Abstractly of Her Experiences with Men -- tThe Way Things Are Done -- t1. A Few Opinions about the Story’s Beginning -- t2. Some Implications -- t3. The Tails’ Confessions -- t4. Mr. Q’s Character -- t5. Madam X Is Up a Creek -- t6. Who Made the First Move? -- t7. How to Wrap Up All the Issues Left Hanging -- t8. The Rationality of the Widow’s Historical Contribution and Status -- t9. The Vague Positions of Mr. Q and Madam X’s Husband -- t10. How We Reversed the Negative and Elected Madam X Our Representative -- t11. Madam X’s Steps Are Buoyant; On Broad Five Spice Street, She Walks toward Tomorrow0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFive Spice Street tells the story of a street in an unnamed city whose inhabitants speculate on the life of a mysterious Madam X. The novel interweaves their endless suppositions into a work that is at once political parable and surreal fantasia. Some think X is 50 years old; others that she is 22. Some believe she has occult powers and has thereby enslaved the young men of the street; others think she is a clever trickster playing mind games with the common people. Who is Madam X? How has she brought the good people of Five Spice Street to their knees either in worship or in exasperation? The unknown narrator takes no sides in the endless interplay of visions, arguments, and opinions. The investigation rages, as the street becomes a Walpurgisnacht of speculations, fantasies, and prejudices. Madam X is a vehicle whereby the people bare their souls, through whom they reveal themselves even as they try to penetrate the mystery of her extraordinary powers.Five Spice Street is one of the most astonishing novels of the past twenty years. Exploring the collective consciousness of this little street of ordinary people, Can Xue penetrates the deepest existential anxieties of the present day-whether in China or in the West-where the inevitable impermanence of identity struggles with the narrative within which identity must compose itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aExistentialismvFiction. 0aIdentity (Philosophical concept)vFiction. 0aStrangersvFiction. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh1 aChen, Zeping, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGernant, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030012227540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014248840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300142488423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300142488/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  